something that's generally not

01:09:04.960 --> 01:09:08.880
common for normal
players, it kind of

01:09:08.880 --> 01:09:12.540
screams that you're not
too attached to the hand.

01:09:12.540 --> 01:09:14.490
And a 2/3 of the
pot bet only really

01:09:14.490 --> 01:09:17.279
needs to win a small percentage
of time to be profitable.

01:09:17.279 --> 01:09:19.670
I get the no one likes
to lose money on a bluff,

01:09:19.670 --> 01:09:26.290
but 1/3 bet works much less
of the time than a 2/3,

01:09:26.290 --> 01:09:29.229
and you actually get much
less value out of it.

01:09:29.229 --> 01:09:30.560
So bet enough.

01:09:30.560 --> 01:09:32.050
Bet like you had a normal hand.

01:09:32.050 --> 01:09:34.540
Bet enough that, if someone
is drawing to something,

01:09:34.540 --> 01:09:37.952
they don't have the
odds to make that call.

01:09:37.952 --> 01:09:39.910
Alternatively, don't bet
too much on the bluff,

01:09:39.910 --> 01:09:42.680
and I'm making pretty
wide ranges here so

01:09:42.680 --> 01:09:46.360
don't think that I'm
contradicting myself here.

01:09:46.360 --> 01:09:49.500
One of the biggest tells for a
bluff is someone betting more

01:09:49.500 --> 01:09:52.569
than the pot, just because
it means they didn't actually

01:09:52.569 --> 01:09:54.420
think through the
numbers, and they're just

01:09:54.420 --> 01:09:57.506
like I want to bet a lot so
that makes the other guy fold.

01:09:57.506 --> 01:09:59.630
But in general, don't bet
too much, and by too much

01:09:59.630 --> 01:10:03.772
I mean more than the pot.

01:10:03.772 --> 01:10:05.480
And in addition, if
you're short stacked,

01:10:05.480 --> 01:10:07.188
don't bluff an amount
that, if he raised,

01:10:07.188 --> 01:10:08.780
you'd have to call anyway.

01:10:08.780 --> 01:10:14.594
In which case, you should
just bet all in there.

01:10:14.594 --> 01:10:16.510
So don't be afraid of
getting caught bluffing.

01:10:16.510 --> 01:10:18.710
So this is a reason
people don't bluff live.

01:10:18.710 --> 01:10:22.902
It's because they're afraid
of showing down nothing.

01:10:22.902 --> 01:10:23.860
Don't worry about that.

01:10:23.860 --> 01:10:25.906
One of the best indications
to me of someone

01:10:25.906 --> 01:10:28.830
being a good player is they'll
and show down a bad hand

01:10:28.830 --> 01:10:30.147
and just be like, yep.

01:10:30.147 --> 01:10:32.480
That's how you play poker,
and that'll be the end of it.

01:10:32.480 --> 01:10:34.800
So don't worry
about-- what you have

01:10:34.800 --> 01:10:36.590
when you bluff is
completely immaterial.

01:10:36.590 --> 01:10:39.130
So just having a losing
hand that's really bad

01:10:39.130 --> 01:10:41.770
is no different than having
a marginal losing hand.

01:10:41.770 --> 01:10:45.792
So don't be afraid of being
bluffing, especially live.

01:10:45.792 --> 01:10:48.000
People get embarrassed when
they get caught bluffing.

01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:49.840
Don't worry about it.

01:10:49.840 --> 01:10:51.800
So semi-bluffing
is great compared

01:10:51.800 --> 01:10:55.350
to bluffing because you have
a chance of winning the hand,

01:10:55.350 --> 01:10:57.490
but if you're in position,
sometimes it's better

01:10:57.490 --> 01:10:59.270
just to take a free card.

01:10:59.270 --> 01:11:01.040
If he shows weakness
and checks into you

01:11:01.040 --> 01:11:04.260
when you have an open ended
straight drawn, in some cases

01:11:04.260 --> 01:11:06.780
it's just going to be right to
check and get your free card.

01:11:06.780 --> 01:11:08.740
You have to compare
your EV of checking

01:11:08.740 --> 01:11:11.380
to your EV of bluffing.

01:11:11.380 --> 01:11:15.660
And don't bluff calling
stations because a lot

01:11:15.660 --> 01:11:19.650
of your value from these guys
will come from value betting.

01:11:19.650 --> 01:11:21.910
The only way you'll
possibly lose to them

01:11:21.910 --> 01:11:23.650
is if you try to bluff them.

01:11:23.650 --> 01:11:28.040
You might be in
a situation where

01:11:28.040 --> 01:11:29.950
you're ready to run
over calling stations,

01:11:29.950 --> 01:11:32.490
but you don't have good
cards and bluffing is not

01:11:32.490 --> 01:11:33.470
